The President made remarks at the Southern Illinois Airport in response to the recent shooting at a synagogue in Pittsburgh. He expressed his condolences and condemned the act as an anti-Semitic act of terror. He called for the death penalty for individuals who commit such acts and praised the law enforcement response. The President also mentioned the importance of unity and discussed the upcoming midterm elections. He criticized the media for being biased against him and stated that he would change his tone for his upcoming rally. He confirmed that he will be visiting Pittsburgh in the aftermath of the shooting.